    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When Adam was one hundred and thirty, [[COMMENT(0)]] he fathered
        a child in his own likeness and in his own image, and he named him Seth. '
      comments:
      - number: 5:3
        content: "  Or \u201Ctwo hundred and thirty\u201D (LXX, Sam. Pent.). The
          ages given of individuals in this chapter are taken from the Hebrew. Both
          the Septuagint and Samaritan Pentateuch give different ages, usually adding
          one hundred years to each.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Adam lived an additional eight hundred years after Seth was born
        and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The life span of Adam was nine hundred and thirty years, and then
        he died. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 5:5
        content: '  People experienced lengthy life spans in the antediluvian age.
          It is plausible that Adam and Noah knew each other, since their lives overlapped
          243 years. Perhaps Adam orally passed down the creation story to his entire
          lineage, including Noah. One Jewish tradition states that Adam had three
          hundred sons and daughters. The history of man begins with death and pain,
          but will one day end with delight and pleasure, as the redeemed become
          the dwelling place of God.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When Seth was one hundred and five, he fathered Enosh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Seth lived an additional eight hundred and seven years after Enosh
        was born and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: The life span of Seth was nine hundred and twelve years, and then
        he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When Enosh was ninety, he fathered Kenan. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:9
        content: "  The probable meaning of    is \u201Cone who laments [over death
          or dying].\u201D    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Enosh lived an additional eight hundred and fifteen years after Kenan
        was born and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: The life span of Enosh was nine hundred and five years, and then he
        died.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When Kenan was seventy, he fathered Mahalalel. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:12
        content: "    means \u201Cthe splendor of God\u201D or \u201Cpraising God.\u201D    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Kenan lived an additional eight hundred and forty years after Mahalalel
        was born and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The life span of Kenan was nine hundred and ten years, and then he
        died.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When Mahalalel was sixty-five, he fathered Jared. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:15
        content: "  Or \u201CYered.\u201D    means \u201Cto descend\u201D or possibly
          \u201Cservant.\u201D    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Mahalalel lived an additional eight hundred and thirty years after
        Jared was born and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The life span of Mahalalel was eight hundred and ninety-five years,
        and then he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'When Jared was one hundred and sixty-two, he fathered Enoch. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:18
        content: "    means \u201Che teaches,\u201D \u201Che initiates,\u201D or
          \u201Cdedicated one.\u201D As the seventh from Adam, the life of Enoch
          teaches us what a life of dedication to God looks like. Enoch shows us
          what mature sonship could be. He was a prophet who foretold the second
          coming (see  ). God told Adam and Eve about the first coming (see  ), yet
          Enoch received even more revelation as he prophesied of the return of Christ.    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Jared lived an additional eight hundred years after Enoch was born
        and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: The life span of Jared was nine hundred and sixty-two years, and then
        he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'When Enoch was sixty-five, he fathered Methuselah. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 5:21
        content: "    is a complex name with at least two words embedded within it:
          \u201Cdeath\u201D and \u201Csend/let go.\u201D Some scholars believe his
          name means \u201Cwhen he dies, it will be sent\u201D or \u201Chis death
          will bring.\u201D This is a prophecy hidden in his name, for the year he
          died was the year God sent the flood. Jewish writers say that Methuselah,
          Noah\u2019s grandfather, died seven days before the flood and that Noah
          and his family entered the ark the day Methuselah died (). For 969 years,
          the world had a walking warning of the coming judgment. An alternate meaning
          of    is \u201Cman of the spear [weapon].\u201D    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Enoch walked with God for three hundred years after Methuselah was
        born and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23-24: '
      title: 
      number: 23-24
      content: Enoch and God walked together as intimate friends; then God took him
        to himself, [[COMMENT(0)]] and he was seen no more. The life span of Enoch
        was three hundred and sixty-five years.
      comments:
      - number: "5:23\u201324"
        content: "  The phrase \u201CGod took him\u201D is the Hebrew word  , which
          can also mean \u201CGod took him in marriage,\u201D as a man takes a bride
          in marriage. Luke included Enoch in the genealogy of the Son of God (see 
          ). He was a man who walked in faith and was translated from earth to heaven
          without dying (apotheosis). His life was pleasing to God (see  ). He also
          was a prophet who prophesied about the coming of Christ with myriads of
          holy ones (see  ). Ancient Jewish and Arabic writings often refer to him
          as one who possessed the secrets of heaven and invented mathematics, astronomy,
          and a lunar-based calendar. The    states that he was carried into paradise,
          where he wrote down the judgment of all men.    "
    - name: '23-24: '
      title: 
      number: 23-24
      content: Enoch and God walked together as intimate friends; then God took him
        to himself, [[COMMENT(0)]] and he was seen no more. The life span of Enoch
        was three hundred and sixty-five years.
      comments:
      - number: "5:23\u201324"
        content: "  The phrase \u201CGod took him\u201D is the Hebrew word  , which
