    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Methuselah was one hundred and eighty-seven, he fathered Lamech. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Methuselah lived an additional seven hundred and eighty-two years
        after Lamech was born and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: The life span of Methuselah was nine hundred and sixty-nine years,
        and then he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'When Lamech was one hundred and eighty-two, he fathered a son '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "and named him Noah, [[COMMENT(0)]] saying, \u201CHe will relieve
        us from our hard work and painful toil, and from the ground that <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        cursed.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 5:29
        content: "  This is a pun, for    and the Hebrew words for \u201Crelief,\u201D
          \u201Ccomfort,\u201D or \u201Crest\u201D are very similar. Noah was the
          tenth generation from Adam. Ten is the biblical number of trial and human
          responsibility (i.e., Ten Words/Commandments,  ). See also  ;  . There
          are ten more generations between Noah and Abraham. Notice the meaning of
          nine of these names of the men of the line of Seth: \u201Cman,\u201D \u201Cappointed,\u201D
          \u201Cmortality,\u201D \u201Clament of death,\u201D \u201Csplendor of God,\u201D
          \u201Cdescends,\u201D \u201Chis death will bring,\u201D \u201Cpowerful-overcoming,\u201D
          \u201Crest and comfort.\u201D When the meanings of these nine names are
          joined together, we find an obvious theme hidden in the genealogy of Adam:
          \u201C  is    to    and the  , but the    (Jesus Christ) will  , and   
          the    of death and sin to bring to us  .\u201D  "
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Lamech lived an additional five hundred and ninety-five years after
        Noah was born and had many other sons and daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The life span of Lamech was seven hundred and seventy-seven years,
        and then he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: After Noah had lived five hundred years, he fathered Shem, Ham, and
        Japheth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Grieves over Human Wickedness'
      title: God Grieves over Human Wickedness
      number: 1
      content: 'When people began to populate the earth, they had many lovely daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Divine beings [[COMMENT(0)]] found them very appealing, so they took
        the women they wanted as their wives.
      comments:
      - number: 6:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe sons of the gods\u201D or \u201Cangels of God\u201D
          (LXX). This is one of the most difficult verses in Genesis to interpret.
          There is much debate over the identity of these  , yet we see that they
          are linked to the \u201CNephilim (giants),\u201D the corrupting of the
          divine \u201Cseed of the woman\u201D who was to come (), and the judgment
          of God through the flood. Many scholars view \u201Cthe sons of the gods\u201D
          as sons of Seth (the godly lineage), but the line of Seth is nowhere stated
          to be a godly line; in fact, only Noah was considered righteous in God\u2019s
          eyes. Other scholars see them as a reference to a group of fallen angels
          \u201Cin rebellion who went outside their rightful domain of authority
          and abandoned their appointed realms\u201D to have sexual relations with
          women (). Consequently, God \u201Cthrew them into the lowest, darkest dungeon
          of gloom and locked them in chains\u201D (). The argument that they could
          not be fallen angels because angels cannot marry (see  ) is in reference
          to angels who are in heaven, not the angels who came to earth as part of
          Satan\u2019s plan to cohabitate with women and corrupt the human race.
          Virtually all of the earliest writings of Jewish and Christian literature
          interpret the phrase \u201Cthe sons of the gods\u201D as heavenly beings
          known as fallen angels or \u201Cwatchers.\u201D See also  ;  ;  ;  ; Dead
          Sea scrolls 1QapGen, 4QDtj and 4QDtq; the Damascus Document 4Q180; the 
          ;  ; the  ; the Jewish historian Josephus; and church fathers Justin Martyr,
          Eusebius, Clement of Alexandria, and Origen. The coming of the Lord (Gr. 
          ) is also going to take place in a time just like the days of Noah (see 
          ).    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "<smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> said, \u201CMy Spirit [[COMMENT(0)]]
        will not strive  with humanity indefinitely,  for they are mortal. Their
        life span will be shortened to only one hundred and twenty years.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 6:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cbreath.\u201D      Or \u201Cshield man [from judgment].\u201D
          Although many scholars translate this hapax legomenon as \u201Cabide,\u201D
          the cognate Akkadian word means to \u201Cshield\u201D or \u201Cprotect.\u201D     
          Or \u201Cforever.\u201D      Or \u201Cthey will only live another one hundred
          and twenty years,\u201D possibly a prophecy of when the flood was coming.    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Back then, and later, there were giants [[COMMENT(0)]] on the earth,
        who were born as a result of the unholy union of heavenly beings with the
        human daughters. They were the mighty ones of old, warriors of renown.
      comments:
      - number: 6:4
        content: "  This is the Hebrew word  . The triliteral root is also used for
          \u201Cfallen ones.\u201D They appear to be the offspring of the \u201Cdivine
          beings\u201D and women (v.  ). They were monsters of iniquity, meant to
          corrupt the earth and destroy the godly \u201Cseed\u201D (). There are
          only two ways to kill giants in the Bible: (1) like David, prophesy their
          downfall, run straight toward them, knock them down, and cut off their
          heads (see  ), or (2) like Caleb and Joshua, conquer them, and see them
          as \u201Cbread\u201D to strengthen us (). See also  . David also raised
          up giant killers among his mighty men (see  ;  ).    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> saw how extremely wicked humanity
        had become, for they imagined only evil, for all they thought about was doing
        evil all the time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> was saddened [[COMMENT(0)]] that
        he had made humanity, and his heart was filled with pain. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:6
        content: "  Or \u201CGod sighed within himself\u201D or \u201CGod regretted.\u201D
          This is the Hebrew word  , which is nearly impossible to translate adequately
          into English. It is a word that expresses grief, comfort, compassion, and
          hope all at the same time. God felt all of these emotions over the creation
          of man. God\u2019s heart was filled with sorrow, compassion, and hope,
          not simply anger.    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> decided, \u201CI will do away with
        my ruined creation\u2014human beings that I created\u2014people and animals,
        creeping things and flying birds, for it breaks my heart that I made them!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Noah Pleases God'
      title: Noah Pleases God
      number: 8
      content: "But one man discovered grace [[COMMENT(0)]] before the face of <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>:
        Noah. <smallcaps>.\u201D It was not the virtue of Noah that saved him, but
        the grace of God. This is the first mention of grace in the Bible.</smallcaps>"
      comments:
      - number: 6:8
        content: "  Or \u201CNoah found favor.\u201D The Hebrew word for \u201Cfavor\u201D
          is the name Noah written backwards, an obvious Hebrew play on words.     
          Noah found another age\u2014the age of grace. He laid hold of grace and
          knew that God was merciful, even in an age of judgment and wickedness.
          It is possible to translate this sentence \u201CNoah laid hold of grace
          in the eyes of      "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'This is the story of Noah.Noah was a godly man of integrity, without
        fault in his generation, [[COMMENT(0)]] and he lived close to God. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:9
        content: '  Ezekiel described Noah as one of the godliest of men (see  , 
          ). No matter how evil the world may be around us, God has enough grace
          to purify our hearts and enable us to live godly lives for his glory.    '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Noah had three sons, Shem, [[COMMENT(0)]] Ham,  and Japheth. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:10
        content: "  Shem, from whom descended the Semitic races, means \u201Cname,\u201D
          \u201Cupright,\u201D \u201Cbrilliant,\u201D \u201Cprosperity,\u201D or
          \u201Cdignity.\u201D According to some Jewish traditions and rabbinical
          teachings, Shem is sometimes identified as Melchizedek (B. Talmud Nedarim
          32b; Genesis Rabbah 46:7; Genesis Rabbah 56:10; Leviticus Rabbah 25:6;
          Numbers Rabbah 4:8). Jesus was a descendant of Shem (see  ). The    mentions
          Shem\u2019s wife, who survived the flood, as Sedeqetelebab. It also states
          that each of Noah\u2019s three sons built cities named after their wives.       
          means \u201Chot,\u201D \u201Che raged,\u201D or \u201Ctumult.\u201D The
          Egyptian word for \u201CHam\u201D is \u201Cservant.\u201D The historian
          Josephus states that the Hamites populated northern Africa and adjoining
          regions of Asia. Egypt is called the land of Ham (see  ,  ). The    mentions
          Ham\u2019s wife, who survived the flood, as Na\u2019eltama\u2019uk. Pakistan
          claims to have Ham\u2019s burial site, and its people considered him to
          be a prophet.        means \u201Clet him spread out,\u201D \u201Cenlargement,\u201D
          \u201Cincrease,\u201D or \u201Cexpansion.\u201D    is taken from a root
          word for \u201Cbeautiful.\u201D He is considered the father of the European,
          Anatolian, and East Asian peoples. In Greek tradition, he is considered
          the ancestor of the Greeks. The    mentions Japheth\u2019s wife as \u2018Adataneses.    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Injustice and violence filled the world; the earth was ruined [[COMMENT(0)]]
        in the sight of God, '
      comments:
      - number: 6:11
        content: '  That is, everyone had corrupted their lives with wickedness.    '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'for he saw how debased the world had become, for everyone was corrupt
        to the core. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "So God said to Noah, [[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CI have decided  that all
        living creatures must die, for their violence has filled the earth, and I
        will wipe them off the face of the earth! "
      comments:
      - number: 6:13
        content: "  God spoke directly with Noah seven times in this narrative.     
          Or \u201CIt is in front of me\u201D or \u201CThe time of every man is come
          before me\u201D (LXX).    "
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: "Build a boat for yourself\u2014an ark [[COMMENT(0)]] of sturdy timber. 
        And this is how you are to design it: make separate compartments  within
        it, and seal  it inside and out with thick tar. The length is to be 450 feet,
        its width 75 feet, and its height 45 feet.   "
      comments:
      - number: "6:14\u201315"
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cark\u201D () is found seven times in
          this chapter and seven times in ch.  .      Or \u201Cgopher wood,\u201D
          possibly cypress or cedar.      Or \u201Cnests.\u201D      This is the
          Hebrew word  , which has a homonym that means \u201Catonement.\u201D Noah
          was told to seal (lit. \u201Catone for\u201D) the ark, as it were, in the
          atonement. Christ\u2019s blood now preserves us from judgment. He endured
          judgment in our place, and we are now sealed until we experience full salvation
          (see  ). This homonym also has the meaning of \u201Chenna.\u201D Jesus
          is like a bouquet of henna (atonement, see  ).      Or \u201C300 cubits
          long [130 meters], 50 cubits wide [22 meters], and 30 cubits high [13 meters].\u201D
          The Hebrew word for \u201Ccubit\u201D literally means \u201Cforearm.\u201D
          The measurement of a cubit is thought to be about 18\u201320 inches (45\u201350
          cm). This suggests a vessel of over 43,000 tons. See A. Heidel,  , 1946,
          p. 236. Even with the smallest estimate for a cubit, the ark would have
          three floors of 33,750 square feet each, making a total space of over 101,000
          square feet.    "
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: "Build a boat for yourself\u2014an ark [[COMMENT(0)]] of sturdy timber. 
        And this is how you are to design it: make separate compartments  within
        it, and seal  it inside and out with thick tar. The length is to be 450 feet,
        its width 75 feet, and its height 45 feet.   "
      comments:
      - number: "6:14\u201315"
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Cark\u201D () is found seven times in
          this chapter and seven times in ch.  .      Or \u201Cgopher wood,\u201D
          possibly cypress or cedar.      Or \u201Cnests.\u201D      This is the
          Hebrew word  , which has a homonym that means \u201Catonement.\u201D Noah
          was told to seal (lit. \u201Catone for\u201D) the ark, as it were, in the
          atonement. Christ\u2019s blood now preserves us from judgment. He endured
          judgment in our place, and we are now sealed until we experience full salvation
          (see  ). This homonym also has the meaning of \u201Chenna.\u201D Jesus
          is like a bouquet of henna (atonement, see  ).      Or \u201C300 cubits
          long [130 meters], 50 cubits wide [22 meters], and 30 cubits high [13 meters].\u201D
          The Hebrew word for \u201Ccubit\u201D literally means \u201Cforearm.\u201D
          The measurement of a cubit is thought to be about 18\u201320 inches (45\u201350
          cm). This suggests a vessel of over 43,000 tons. See A. Heidel,  , 1946,
          p. 236. Even with the smallest estimate for a cubit, the ark would have
          three floors of 33,750 square feet each, making a total space of over 101,000
          square feet.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Cover it with a roof, [[COMMENT(0)]] but leave a gap of eighteen
        inches  at the top for ventilation. Construct a door on the side of the ark,
        and design it with lower, middle, and upper decks. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:16
        content: "  Or \u201CMake a window.\u201D The meaning of the Hebrew word
          is uncertain.      Or \u201Cone cubit\u201D (45\u201360 cm).    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I am going to release a great flood that will destroy all life upon
        the earth, and every breathing thing under heaven will perish\u2014everything
        on earth will die. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But as for you, I will establish my covenant of friendship, and you
        will escape destruction by coming into the ark, [[COMMENT(0)]] you and your
        wife, your sons and their wives. '
      comments:
      - number: 6:18
        content: "  Noah\u2019s ark is a beautiful picture of Jesus Christ. It was
          made from sturdy wood (the humanity of Christ, see  ) and is sealed with
          tar (blood atonement). It was a place of salvation and preservation (Jesus
          our Savior). As man was invited into the ark to find a place of security
          from judgment, so we are hidden in Christ (see  ). All who entered the
          ark were kept safe and none perished. The dimensions of the ark are significant.
          It was 300 cubits long (300 is the number of complete victory in Christ
          [see  ;  ;  ]), 50 cubits wide (50 is the number of Jubilee and Pentecost
          [see  ]), and 30 cubits high (30 is the number of maturity, authority,
          and full stature [see  ;  ;  ;  ], and priests began their ministry at
          30). The ark only had one door, and there is only one door of salvation
          (see  ;  ). The door was on the side of the ark, and Jesus\u2019 side was
          pierced (see  ). There were three stories or levels to Noah\u2019s ark,
          which points to a full salvation for man\u2019s body, soul, and spirit
          (see  ; Noah\u2019s family lived on the third level). There were many rooms
          (\u201Ccompartments\u201D) in the ark, and there are many rooms in the
          Father\u2019s house (; see  ). The ark came to rest in the seventh month
          on the seventeenth day. The Passover was the fourteenth day of the seventh
          month, and three days later (the seventeenth day) was the resurrection
          (Christ \u201Cresting\u201D on high). The ark rested on Mt. Ararat, which
          means \u201Cthe curse is reversed\u201D or \u201Chigh and holy land.\u201D
          To be \u201Cin the ark\u201D is to be \u201Cin Christ\u201D (see  ). The
          Bible mentions three arks, and each point to Christ: Noah\u2019s ark, the
          ark for baby Moses (see  ), and the ark of the covenant (see  ).    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Bring with you into the ark a pair of every animal, male and female;
        and they will also be spared. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Different kinds of birds, animals large and small [[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014two
        of every kind I will send to you to be kept alive. "
      comments:
      - number: 6:20
        content: "  Or \u201Canimals, and creeping things [everything that walks
          or moves on the ground].\u201D    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Also take with you every kind of food, both for you and them.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Noah completed all these preparations and did everything exactly
        as God had commanded him. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 6:22
        content: "  Noah\u2019s response to the grace of God was obedience to his
          commands. This phrase is repeated four times concerning Noah (see  ;  , 
          ,  ). It is God\u2019s grace that leads us to obedience, not independence.
          See  .  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Great Flood'
      title: The Great Flood
      number: 1
      content: "The day came when  <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> said to Noah, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        \u201CCome  into the ark, you and your entire household, for I have found
        you to be the only one righteous in my eyes in this generation.   "
      comments:
      - number: 7:1
        content: "  How did God speak to Noah? Did he come in human form? Perhaps
          he appeared in a burning bush, or as an angel, or in a dream. God is able
          to speak in whatever way he chooses. We have a God who speaks to those
          whose ways are blameless. Noah moved with faith and acted on the revelation
          given to him. Do you respond when God speaks?      The implication is that
          God was in the ark waiting for Noah to enter and come to him. He has always
          gone before us and knows what we will face. This Hebrew word for \u201Ccome\u201D
          is used in contemporary Jewish weddings and songs\u2014\u201Ccome to me.\u201D     
          This statement shows that the sons of Seth could not rightly be called
          the sons of God (see  ), for only Noah was righteous. God needed Noah.
          There had to be a righteous man who would save mankind. When God comes
          down, he comes looking for human vessels he can use to bring deliverance
          and salvation (see  ;  ).    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Take with you seven pairs of all the clean animals, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        both male and female, and one pair of all the unclean animals, both male
        and female. '
      comments:
      - number: 7:2
        content: '  Seven pairs of clean animals (ritually acceptable) were spared
          so that Noah could use them for sacrifices. See  .    '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Take seven pairs of flying birds of all kinds, male and female, to
        make sure they survive on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For in seven days I will send rain and flood the earth for forty
        days and forty nights. [[COMMENT(0)]] Every living thing that I made I will
        wipe off the face of the earth.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 7:4
        content: '  The number forty is a symbolic number in the Bible that represents
          testing and purification. See  ;  ;  ;  ;  .      In the days of Noah,
          the flood took away the wicked and left behind the righteous. See  ;  .    '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: Noah obeyed all that <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> had commanded him.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Noah was six hundred years old when the great flood came on the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Noah and his wife and his sons and their wives boarded the ark to
        escape the flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: 'Two of each animal, the male and female, clean and unclean, large
        and small, along with birds and crawling things, entered the ark with Noah
        as God had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8-9: '
      title: 
      number: 8-9
      content: 'Two of each animal, the male and female, clean and unclean, large
        and small, along with birds and crawling things, entered the ark with Noah
        as God had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Then seven days later, massive floodwaters covered the earth.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "It started in the six hundredth year of Noah\u2019s life, in the
        second month on the seventeenth day. [[COMMENT(0)]]  On that day, all the
        fountains  of the subterranean deep cracked open and burst up through the
        ground. Heaven\u2019s floodgates were opened,   "
      comments:
      - number: 7:11
        content: "  The exact date of the deluge is given, a miracle pointing to
          the divine inspiration of Scripture. God noted and had recorded the exact
          day the flood began. He gave us amazing details of these events as they
          happened. The flood began, according to the Jewish scribes, in the year
          1656 from creation.      The Hebrew word  , or \u201Cfountains,\u201D here
          has the same root as    in  . As our inward lives sprout and bring forth
          fruit, it has the power of a subterranean fountain.      It is as though
          God returned the earth back to the chaos of ch.  . He once separated the
          waters and raised up the dry ground; now he was covering the earth again
          with water and removing the separation that he spoke into existence (see 
          ).    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: and heavy rains fell on the earth for forty days and forty nights.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 7:12
        content: "  God, at creation, had fixed a \u201Cboundary\u201D for the waters
          (), setting doors and bars in place that the waters could not pass (see 
          ). Now he simply removed those restraints, and the waters gushed forth
          and flooded the earth as they had done at first (see  ). The floodgates
          of the heavens were similarly opened up.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'On that very day, Noah and his wife, their sons, Ham, Shem, and Japheth,
        and their wives, entered safely into the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: "Pairs of every species of animal entered with them\u2014wild animals,
        domesticated animals, large and small, and every species of bird and winged
        creatures\u2014every animal that has the breath of life came into the ark
        with Noah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14-15: '
      title: 
      number: 14-15
      content: "Pairs of every species of animal entered with them\u2014wild animals,
        domesticated animals, large and small, and every species of bird and winged
        creatures\u2014every animal that has the breath of life came into the ark
        with Noah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Both male and female went inside as God had commanded Noah; and <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>
        himself shut them in. [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps>
      comments:
      - number: 7:16
        content: "  Closing the door of the ark was a supernatural act of God. It
          was Elohim (\u201Cthe Mighty One\u201D) who commanded Noah to enter the
          ark, and  (the covenant-keeping God, the Friend of Sinners) who shut him
          in. The God of Israel is known by both names.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For forty days, the flood engulfed the earth. The swelling floodwaters
        lifted up the ark until it rose high above the ground. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The raging flood completely inundated the earth, but the ark floated
        safely, drifting upon the surface of the water, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'until the highest mountains were completely submerged beneath the
        rising waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The waters rose over twenty-two feet [[COMMENT(0)]] above the highest
        mountains.   '
      comments:
      - number: 7:20
        content: "  Or \u201Cfifteen cubits [22.5 feet; 6.86 meters].\u201D Waters
          covered the earth at a depth of three miles above sea level. All the mountains
          of the pride of man were covered up. Who measured all these things? Who
          knew the mountains were covered by fifteen cubits? It could not have been
          Noah or Moses, unless God showed them. The amazing details of the account
          of the flood all point to the divine inspiration of Scripture.      This
          indicates a universal flood, not just a regional one. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Every living thing on the earth perished\u2014domesticated animals,
        wild animals, birds, everything that moved on the earth, and all mankind
        perished. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Everything perished\u2014every animal on earth with the breath of
        life in its nostrils died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "All life on earth was blotted out\u2014all that he had made, animals
        large and small, wild and domesticated, birds and reptiles, including humanity,
        was wiped off the face of the earth. Only Noah was left behind, [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and those who were in the ark with him. "
      comments:
      - number: 7:23
        content: '  In the days of Noah, the wicked were taken away, swept off the
          earth by the flood. It was the righteous who were left behind to inherit
          the earth. See  ;  .  '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the waters covered the earth for 150 days.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Noah Leaves the Ark'
      title: Noah Leaves the Ark
      number: 1
      content: "God\u2019s heart was moved with compassion as he remembered [[COMMENT(0)]]
        Noah and all the animals, large and small,  that were with him in the ark. 
        And God caused a wind  to sweep across the earth again   and the waters subsided. "
      comments:
      - number: 8:1
        content: "  God had not forgotten and then suddenly remembered them; his
          heart of compassion focused on Noah and all that survived in the ark. Mercy
          triumphs over judgment (see  ).      Or \u201Cwild and domesticated animals.\u201D     
          Being in the ark assured their salvation. Being in Christ likewise assures
          our salvation.      Or \u201C[his] Spirit\u201D or \u201Cbreath.\u201D
          See  .      God repeated what he did at creation; his Spirit hovered over
          the face of the waters. And it happened again thousands of years later,
          as God\u2019s Spirit hovered over and filled 120 believers at Pentecost,
          giving them new creation life.    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He closed the subterranean fountains and the floodgates of heaven
        and held back the rain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'After 150 days, the floodwaters gradually receded from the earth
        and the waters began to subside. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And on the seventeenth day of the seventh month, [[COMMENT(0)]] the
        ark came to rest  on the highest peak in Ararat.   '
      comments:
      - number: 8:4
        content: "  At the institution of the Feast of Passover, the Lord made the
          seventh month into the first month, the month of great importance for Israel
          (see  ). Passover was the fourteenth day of the month. Three days later
          would be the seventeenth day of the month; the very day Jesus rose from
          the dead. The final resting place of our ark of salvation was the top of
          the mountain. Jesus was raised on high, seated at the right hand of the
          Most High. What inspiration lies within the Bible!      This is a play
          on words, for Noah\u2019s name means \u201Crest.\u201D God\u2019s covenant
          of peace with Noah would remain (see  ;  ).      Mt. Ararat is believed
          to be on the border of Turkey, Armenia, and Iran, known as Urartu in Assyrian
          inscriptions. See  ;  ;  .    means \u201Cthe curse is reversed\u201D or
          \u201Chigh and holy land.\u201D The resting place of God\u2019s sons and
          daughters is where \u201Cthe curse is reversed\u201D (the cross and empty
          tomb), in the \u201Chigh and holy land\u201D of being seated with Christ
          in the heavenly realm (see  ).    "
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: The waters continued to recede until the tenth month. And on the first
        day of the tenth month, all the mountaintops appeared. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:5
        content: '  The mountaintops became visible seventy-three days after the
          ark rested. This new age now begins with eight people. Eight is the biblical
          number of a new beginning.    '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'After forty more days Noah opened the window he had made in the ark '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: and released a raven. It flew back and forth from the ark until the
        earth was dry. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:7
        content: '  In other words, the unclean raven apparently did not return to
          the ark.    '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then he sent out a dove [[COMMENT(0)]] to see if the waters had receded
        from the surface of the ground. '
      comments:
      - number: 8:8
        content: "  Or \u201Csent out a dove from him,\u201D an awkward construction
          in English. The next verse shows that Noah took the dove back into the
          ark with his hand to see if there was any clay or mud on its feet.    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But the dove found no place to rest, so it returned to Noah in the
        ark because the waters still covered the face of the earth. Noah put out
        his hand and grasped the dove and put it back into the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He waited another seven days and released the dove from the ark again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Before evening, the dove came back to him\u2014and there in its beak
        was a freshly plucked olive leaf! [[COMMENT(0)]] So Noah realized that the
        waters had finally subsided from the earth."
      comments:
      - number: 8:11
        content: "  The contrast of the raven and the dove is an allegory. The raven
          symbolizes the law, which was sent out first, but gave no assurance that
          waters of judgment had lifted. The dove, returning with an olive branch,
          a symbol of peace, symbolizes the gospel of grace given to us by the Holy
          Spirit. The gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ brings a better hope to the
          believer\u2014judgment has retreated. Every time the \u201CDove\u201D of
          God comes, he brings a fresh olive branch\u2014fresh oil for the sons and
          daughters of the Most High.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Then he waited another seven days and sent the dove out again, but
        this time it did not return to him in the ark. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:12
        content: '  The Dove (Holy Spirit) cannot rest where there is corruption
          and death. For generations, the Dove, seeking a place to rest, flew over
          Abraham, Moses, the prophets, and the kings unable to find a resting place.
          Until at last, at the river Jordan, the Dove came from the open heavens
          and rested on the perfect man, Jesus, the Son of God (see  ). Has the gentle
          Dove found a nest in your heart? In order to have the gifts (see  ) and
          power of the Dove, you must seek first the nature of the Lamb.    '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "In Noah\u2019s six hundred and first year, on the first day of the
        first month, the waters were dried up from the earth. Noah lifted the hatch,
        looked out, and saw the dry ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'On the twenty-seventh day of the second month, the earth was dry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then God said [[COMMENT(0)]] to Noah, '
      comments:
      - number: 8:15
        content: '  Noah was obedient to God, refusing to move until he heard the
          Word of the Lord. Just as he waited for the command to enter, he waited
          for the command to disembark.    '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CCome out of the ark, you and your wife, your sons, and their
        wives. [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: 8:16
        content: "  Noah waited over six weeks in the ark on top of Ararat for the
          waters to completely recede, and for the ground to dry. This took great
          discipline, for no one likes to wait. But God\u2019s timing is always perfect.
          Noah was in the ark for a total of one year and seventeen days.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Release all the animals with you and set them free\u2014birds, animals
        large and small\u2014every living thing. And they will multiply and abound
        and flourish on the earth and in the sky.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So Noah and his family left the ark; '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: God\u2019s Promise to Noah"
      title: "God\u2019s Promise to Noah"
      number: 19
      content: and every animal large and small, every bird and crawling thing came
        out of the ark by families. [[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: 8:19
        content: "  That is, by species. Noah and his family would never forget the
          moment they pushed open the door of the ark and walked out into a new world.
          Eight human beings found a new beginning with God. Like a new Adam and
          a new Eve, they began all over again. What a spine-tingling moment it was!
          The bright sunlight, the fresh air, the gentle breeze\u2014God had seen
          them through!    "
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Noah erected an altar dedicated to <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>. Noah realized the great love of God that was upon
        his life and offered himself to God. The kindness of God is also seen in
        Jesus. God is always ready to renew a relationship with people when they
        turn to him.</smallcaps> Then he selected ritually clean animals and birds
        of every species and offered them as burnt sacrifices on the altar. '
      comments:
      - number: 8:20
        content: '  The first thing Noah did when he got out of the ark was worship      '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And when <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps> smelled the sweet fragrance
        of Noah\u2019s offerings, his heart was stirred, [[COMMENT(0)]] and he said,
        \u201CNever again will I curse the earth because of people, even though the
        imagination of their hearts are evil from their childhood; nor will I ever
        again destroy every living creature as I have done. I promise this:"
      comments:
      - number: 8:21
        content: "  Or \u201Che said to his heart.\u201D  "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAs long as earth existsthere will always be seasonsof planting
        and harvest,cold and heat,summer and winter,day and night.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Covenant with Noah"
      title: "God\u2019s Covenant with Noah"
      number: 1
      content: "God lovingly blessed Noah and all his family and said to them, \u201CReproduce,
        be fruitful, and populate the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I will cause every living creature of earth, sky, and sea [[COMMENT(0)]]
        to fear and dread you from this time forward. They are now under your authority.   '
      comments:
      - number: 9:2
        content: "  Or \u201Cevery animal of the earth, every bird of the air, everything
          that creeps on the ground, and all the fish of the sea.\u201D      Or \u201Care
          delivered into your hands.\u201D    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You may now eat the meat of animals [[COMMENT(0)]] as well as green
        plants; I now give you everything for food for you. '
      comments:
      - number: 9:3
        content: "  Or \u201Cevery moving thing that lives.\u201D See  ;  .    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'However, you must not eat meat with its lifeblood still in it, for
        its life is in the blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "If anyone takes another person\u2019s life, I will demand an account\u2014whether
        from man or beast, I will demand an account for taking a human life."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CWhoever sheds human blood,by other humans he must have his
        own blood shed;for to kill a person is to kill one madein God\u2019s own
        beautiful image."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now all of you, with my blessing, reproduce,be fruitful and repopulate
        the earth.\u201D [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:7
        content: "  Or \u201Cswarm throughout the earth.\u201D    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then God said to Noah and his family, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CI establish my loving covenant [[COMMENT(0)]] with you, your
        descendants, "
      comments:
      - number: 9:9
        content: "  The Hebrew word for \u201Ccovenant\u201D is    and is found numerous
          times in this chapter. God\u2019s covenant turns judgment into grace.    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and every living creature that is with you\u2014animals large and
        small, birds, and every living thing that came out of the ark. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Rainbow'
      title: The Rainbow
      number: 11
      content: "I will maintain my loving covenant with you. I will never again completely
        destroy life on earth by means of a flood. Yes, never again will a flood
        destroy the whole earth!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CHere is the sign for you and future generations that my loving
        covenant will endure between me and you and every animal that came with you
        out of the ark: "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I have placed my rainbow [[COMMENT(0)]] among the clouds, and it
        will be a sign of my loving covenant between me and the earth. '
      comments:
      - number: 9:13
        content: "  Or \u201Cbending,\u201D most often translated \u201Cwarrior\u2019s
          bow,\u201D for just as a warrior hangs up his bow after the battle, so
          God\u2019s bow, without arrows, is now surrendered to the sky, not aimed
          at earth, because of his love for humanity. The rainbow around God\u2019s
          throne is a full circle, for the earth does not cut off God\u2019s rainbow
          promises. And it is an emerald-colored rainbow around the throne, for it
          is the promise of life. See  ;  .    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Whenever I bring clouds over the earth, and the rainbow appears in
        the clouds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will remember my covenant with you and with every living thing
        upon the earth. Never again will the waters become a flood to destroy life
        from the earth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "When the rainbow is in the clouds, I will see it and remember the
        everlasting covenant I made with you and every living thing of every kind
        upon the earth.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: "17: Noah\u2019s Sons"
      title: "Noah\u2019s Sons"
      number: 17
      content: "So God said to Noah, \u201CThe rainbow is my signature in the sky,
        my seal of love [[COMMENT(0)]] to confirm that I have kept my covenant between
        me and every living thing on earth.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 9:17
        content: "  Or \u201Csign of confirmation.\u201D    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Noah\u2019s sons came out of the ark with him: Shem, Ham (the father
        of Canaan), and Japheth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: From these three sons of Noah the entire world was repopulated.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Noah, a farmer, was the first to plant a vineyard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He drank so much of the wine he made that he got drunk and passed
        out naked inside his tent. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 9:21
        content: '  Chronologically, this would likely have been years after they
          exited the ark.    '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Ham, the father of Canaan, went into the tent and gazed on his
        shamefully exposed father. [[COMMENT(0)]] Then he went out and informed his
        brothers. '
      comments:
      - number: 9:22
        content: '  Various Hebrew scholars surmise that this was a euphemistic account
          of Ham doing some act of gross indecency, not mere voyeurism. See  ;  .    '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So, Shem and Japheth took their father\u2019s cloak [[COMMENT(0)]]
        and walked backwards with the cloak on their shoulders into the tent to cover
        up their naked father. Respectfully, they turned their faces away so as not
        to see their father lying there exposed. "
      comments:
      - number: 9:23
        content: "  Or \u201Cthe garment.\u201D It is possible that Ham brought his
          father\u2019s garment outside the tent to show it to his brothers.    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Noah sobered up and realized what his youngest son had done
        to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "he uttered these words:\u201CCursed be your son, Canaan, [[COMMENT(0)]]and
        let him be the lowest of servants  to his brothers.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: 9:25
        content: "  Although it was Ham, Noah\u2019s son, who violated his father,
          Ham\u2019s son Canaan was the one who was cursed. Some see the possibility
          that Canaan was complicit in what Ham did.      Or \u201Cslave of slaves.\u201D
          Canaan was the ancestor of the Canaanites.    means \u201Cbow down.\u201D
          See  ;  .    "
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He also said,\u201CWorthy of praise is <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>,the
        God of Shem! [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>.</smallcaps>Let Canaan be Shem\u2019s
        slave."
      comments:
      - number: 9:26
        content: '  Jesus Christ came through the lineage of Shem (see  ), the father
          of the Semitic peoples. This is a prophecy that Shem would have a special
          relationship with      '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "May God enlarge Japheth\u2019s familyand increase his territory.
        [[COMMENT(0)]]May he share in the blessing of Shem,and his descendants make
        their homesamong the tents of Shem, and may Canaan be his slave also!\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 9:27
        content: "  Or \u201CMay God make room for Japheth.\u201D This a play on
          words, for the Hebrew triliteral root for    () is identical to the root
          for \u201Cmake room,\u201D \u201Cincrease,\u201D or \u201Cenlarge [enrich,
          prosper].\u201D Japheth was to become the father of enlarged nations, spreading
          out over the globe.      Many scholars view this as an alliance between
          Shem and Japheth that would include sharing the blessing of prosperity
          among them.      This account of Noah\u2019s cursing and blessing of his
          three sons illustrates the power of a father\u2019s words over his children
          (and grandchildren) and how those words create the reality of their future.
          Descendants of each of Noah\u2019s sons were present at the crucifixion
          of the Lord Jesus. The descendants of Shem were present in the Jewish religious
          leaders who conspired to crucify the Messiah. Japheth was present in the
          Romans who participated jointly with the Jews to crucify the Lord Jesus.
          And a descendant of Ham was present in the person of Simon of Cyrene, who
          bore the cross of Christ in servitude (see  ). The sons of Noah are brought
          before us again in  . The Ethiopian was a descendant of Ham whom Philip
          blessed with the gospel (see  ). Saul of Tarsus (Paul) was from Shem and
          was also converted by the revelation of Jesus (see  ). Cornelius the centurion
          was a son of Japheth who believed the good news of Christ (see  ).    "
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'After the flood, Noah lived another three hundred and fifty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Noah\u2019s entire lifetime was nine hundred and fifty years, and
        then he died. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 9:29
        content: "  There are numerous parallels between Noah and Adam. Both came
          onto an earth that had been submerged by water. Both were given lordship
          over creation. Both were blessed and told to multiply. Both were men of
          the soil, working the ground. Both sinned in a garden (vineyard). Both
          experienced the exposure of nakedness. Both men\u2019s sins affected their
          posterity. Both had three sons. And both experienced a prophecy following
          their fall.  "
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Descendants of Japheth'
      title: Descendants of Japheth
      number: 1
      content: "This is the story of the descendants of Noah\u2019s three sons, Shem,
        Ham, and Japheth. After the great flood, they fathered many children. [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:1
        content: "  This begins the second ten-generation account in Genesis, and
          it is incredibly important for understanding human history. This chapter
          contains what many have described as the \u201CTable of Nations,\u201D
          the earliest ethnological table found in the literature of the ancient
          world. Virtually all the names included here have been verified and found
          in archeological sites over the past one hundred years. There are precisely
          seventy names mentioned here, and seventy followers of Jesus were sent
          out as a testimony that the gospel of his kingdom is meant for all people
          (see  ). This chapter includes more than the names of people; it lists
          the names of cities, tribes, and nations. The underlying theme in this
          chapter is that God determines the boundaries of nations and the seasons
          of history. See  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The sons of Japheth were Gomer, [[COMMENT(0)]] Magog,  Madai,  Javan, 
        Tubal,  Meshech,  and Tiras. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:2
        content: "    means \u201Ccomplete\u201D and was the ancestor of the ancient
          Cimmerians who are believed to have originated in southern Russia and northern
          Iran. Gomer is mentioned in    as an ally of Gog and enemy of Israel. Romans,
          Gauls, Germans, Celts, Armenians, and Britons could all be considered as
          descendants of Japheth and Gomer.        means \u201Cregion of Gog,\u201D
          and became the Scythian (Iranian) or Tartar (Russian) tribe. One church
          father, Jerome, states they were \u201CScythian nations, fierce and innumerable,
          who live beyond the Caucasus and the Lake Maeotis, and near the Caspian
          Sea, and spread out even onward to India.\u201D It is possible that the
          Chinese, Japanese, Alaskans, Russians, and Native Americans could be traced
          back as descendants of Japheth and Magog.        means \u201Cmiddle land\u201D
          and was the ancestor of the Medes who lived east of Assyria, south of the
          Caspian Sea. It is possible that the descendants of Madai (the Medes) also
          include the Persians. See  ;  ;  ,  .        means \u201CIonia\u201D or
          \u201CGreece\u201D and is the ancestor of a branch of Greek people.       
          means \u201Cbrought forth\u201D and in contemporary scholarship is identified
          as Tabal, an Anatolian state and region north of the Black Sea, identified
          in Assyrian sources. There is a city in Russia named \u201CTubolsk.\u201D       
          means \u201Cdrawing out\u201D and was the ancestor of a people identified
          by Assyrian records as the \u201CMuscu\u201D and by Josephus as the Cappadocian
          \u201CMosocheni\u201D (or \u201CMushki,\u201D possibly Moscow).      Tiras,
          or Tirana, meaning \u201Cdesire,\u201D was the ancestor of the Thracians,
          who were also called \u201CSea People.\u201D According to the  , they inhabited
          four islands in the Mediterranean. They possibly include the people who
          settled in the Balkans, Romania, Bulgaria, Moravia, and Italy.    "
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Gomer were Ashkenaz, [[COMMENT(0)]] Riphath,  and Togarmah. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:3
        content: "    means \u201Cscattered\u201D and was the ancestor of the northern
          Indo-Germanic tribes and the father of the Saxons and Scandinavians.       
          means \u201Cspoken\u201D and was the ancestor of those that settled in
          Carpathia and Paphlagonia.        means \u201Cyou will break her.\u201D    "
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The sons of Javan were Elishah, [[COMMENT(0)]] Tarshish,  Cyprus, 
        and Rhodes. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:4
        content: "    means \u201CGod of the coming,\u201D or \u201CGod of the coming
          one,\u201D and he was the ancestor of those who populated modern-day Cyprus.
          He is mentioned in    as the source of the purple dye shipped to Tyre.       
          means \u201Cyellow stone\u201D and is mentioned twenty-eight times in the
          Bible but is difficult to identify. Some believe he was the ancestor of
          those who settled in southern Turkey, although there is evidence that Tarshish
          was the ancestor of Sardinia or Tartessus (in Spain). See  ;  ;  .     
          Or \u201CKittim,\u201D which means \u201Cbruisers\u201D and is an ancient
          name for Cyprus. There is a Cyprian city named Kition.      Or \u201CDodanim\u201D
          or \u201CRodanim\u201D (see  ).    means \u201Cleaders\u201D and is most
          often associated with Greece (e.g., the cities of Rhodes, Dardanelles).    "
    - name: '5: Descendants of Ham'
      title: Descendants of Ham
      number: 5
      content: "All of Japheth\u2019s descendants lived in their respective tribes
        and regions, each group speaking its own language. From there, the people
        spread to distant shores and faraway lands."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sons of Ham [[COMMENT(0)]] were Ethiopia,  Egypt,  Libya,  and
        Canaan. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:6
        content: "  The Hamites are listed in four primary subgroups from south to
          north. The first three are in Africa and last in the land bridge between
          Africa and Asia.      Or \u201CCush\u201D or \u201CKesh\u201D (Egyptian),
          whose descendants settled in Ethiopia and southern Sudan.      Or \u201CMizraim,\u201D
          which means \u201Cland of the Copts,\u201D whose descendants settled in
          Egypt.      Or \u201CPut,\u201D which means \u201Ca bow,\u201D whose descendants
          settled in Libya and possibly Somalia. See  .      The descendants of Canaan
          settled in Palestine (Phoenicia).    "
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The sons of Cush were Seba, [[COMMENT(0)]] Havilah, Sabtah,  Raamah, 
        and Sabteca. The sons of Raamah were Sheba  and Dedan. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:7
        content: "    means \u201Cdrink\u201D and is the ancient name for Mero\xEB
          in northeast Africa. See  ;  .      This is the only place Sabtah (\u201Cstriking\u201D)
          is mentioned in the Bible. It is likely a region in southern Arabia.       
          means \u201Chorse\u2019s mane\u201D and is perhaps a south Arabian city
          mentioned in ancient inscriptions. See  .      The descendants of Sabteca
          settled eastward in Samudake, along the Persian Gulf.      The descendants
          of Sheba, which means \u201Can oath,\u201D were the Sabaeans who lived
          in southwest Arabia and were trading merchants. See  .      The descendants
          of Dedan, which means \u201Clowlands,\u201D are mentioned as traders with
          caravans of camels. See  ;  ;  . Dedan may be identified as the modern-day
          oasis of Al-\u2018Ula in northern Arabia or possibly Kuwait.    "
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Cush also had a son named Nimrod, who became known as the first mighty
        conqueror. [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: 10:8
        content: "  Or \u201Cstrong man\u201D or \u201Cgiant\u201D (LXX).    "
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "He was a mighty despot before <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>  [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>.\u201D
        Nimrod was a hunter of men (not simply animals), a potentate, and a terrorist.
        See</smallcaps>. There was a saying, \u201CLike Nimrod, a mighty despot before
        <smallcaps>Yahweh</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: 10:9
        content: "  Or \u201Ca mighty hunter before    . Some etymological studies
          link Nimrod to the word for \u201Crebel\u201D or \u201Cwe will rebel.\u201D
          Nimrod was the first despot and anarchist. Many believe that Nimrod was
          also named \u201CMarduk,\u201D whom scholars identify as the god of the
          Babylonian religions. His wife was Semiramis. They bore a child that is
          identified by some as the Egyptian Osiris and the Hindu Vishnu. See  .    "
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The centers of his kingdom [[COMMENT(0)]], Babel,  Erech,  and Akkad, 
        were in the land of Shinar.   '
      comments:
      - number: 10:10
        content: "  Or \u201CThe beginnings of his kingdom.\u201D      Or \u201CBabylon,\u201D
          which means \u201Cconfusion,\u201D \u201Cmixed,\u201D or \u201Cchaos.\u201D
          Babel was a famous city on the Euphrates in modern Iraq.      A region
          southeast of Babylon known as \u201CUruk\u201D (modern Warka).    means
          \u201Clong.\u201D      A city north of Babylon known as \u201CAgade.\u201D   
          means \u201Csubtle.\u201D      Or \u201CBabylonia.\u201D    "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'From there, he went into Assyria and built the cities of Nineveh,
        [[COMMENT(0)]] Rehoboth-Ir,  Calah,   '
      comments:
      - number: 10:11
        content: "  Nineveh, which means \u201Cabode of the god Ninus,\u201D was
          the capital of Assyria and is located 250 miles northwest of Baghdad. It
          is presently identified with the mounds of Kuyunjik and Nebi Yunus, which
          means \u201Cthe prophet Jonah.\u201D        means \u201C[city of] broad
          streets.\u201D      Calah, which means \u201Centhusiasm,\u201D was one
          of the four great cities of Assyria.    "
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: and Resen [[COMMENT(0)]] (which is between the great city of Calah 
        and Nineveh).
      comments:
      - number: 10:12
        content: "  Resen, which means \u201Cfountainhead,\u201D was one of the four
          great cities of Assyria.      This is modern Nimrud in Iraq, south of Mosul.
          It is likely called \u201Cthe great city\u201D because it was at one time
          the royal capital of the Assyrians.    "
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Egypt [[COMMENT(0)]] was the father of the Ludites,  Anamites,  Lehabites, 
        Naphtuhites,   '
      comments:
      - number: 10:13
        content: "  Or \u201CMizraim.\u201D      The Ludites, which means \u201Cfirebrands,\u201D
          are difficult to identify. They were known as warriors and descendants
          of the Egyptian people. Some scholars see them as Lybians and others as
          Lydians.      The Anamites, which means \u201Caffliction of the waters,\u201D
          were an unidentified people who were descendants of Egypt.      The Lehabites
          were considered descendants of Libya. See  ;  ;  .        may mean \u201Cpeople
          of the [Nile] delta.\u201D    "
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Pathrusites, [[COMMENT(0)]] Casluhites, and Caphtorites (the ancestors
        of the Philistines). '
      comments:
      - number: 10:14
        content: "  The Pathrusites (related to the word  , meaning \u201Csouthland\u201D)
          were inhabitants of Upper Egypt. See  .      Some scholars link this parenthetical
          information with the previously noted Casluhites. The Philistines were
          from the area of the Aegean Sea and invaded the lands of Canaan and Egypt
          in the thirteenth century BC. See  .    "
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Canaan was the father of Sidon [[COMMENT(0)]] (his firstborn), the
        Hittites,   '
      comments:
      - number: 10:15
        content: "  Sidon, which means \u201Chunting,\u201D likely represents all
          of Phoenicia. See  ;  ;  .      Or \u201CHeth\u201D (which means \u201Cterror\u201D),
          the father of the Hittites, a dominant tribe in Canaan.    "
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the Jebusites, [[COMMENT(0)]] the Amorites,  the Girgashites,   '
      comments:
      - number: 10:16
        content: "  The Jebusites, which means \u201Cpeople of the threshing floor,\u201D
          were the ancient inhabitants of Jebus, a stronghold that was conquered
          by David when he established Jerusalem. David purchased the plot of land
          upon which the temple would later be built from Araunah, the Jebusite.
          See  ;  ;  .      The Amorites, which means \u201Ctalkers,\u201D inhabited
          the promised land west of the Jordan before the arrival of the Israelites.
          See  .      The Girgashites, which means \u201Cclay-dwellers,\u201D lived
          to the east of Lake Galilee.    "
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the Hivites, [[COMMENT(0)]] the Arkites,  the Sinites,   '
      comments:
      - number: 10:17
        content: "  The Hivites, which means \u201Cvillagers,\u201D were located
          in the vicinity of Gibeon (see  ;  ) near Shechem (see  ) and near Mt.
          Hermon (see  ).      Beginning with the Arkites, which means \u201Cgnawing,\u201D
          vv.    list inhabitants of cities. The Arkites are identified with modern
          Arqa in Lebanon.      The Sinites, which means \u201Cthose of clay,\u201D
          are connected to an unidentified city, likely near Arqa in Lebanon. See 
          .    "
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the Arvadites, [[COMMENT(0)]] the Zemarites,  and the Hamathites. 
        The families of the Canaanites eventually scattered across '
      comments:
      - number: 10:18
        content: "  The Arvadites, which means \u201Cthose who break loose,\u201D
          are connected to a coastal city in Lebanon, known today as Ruad. See  , 
          .      The Zemarites, which means \u201Cdouble woolen,\u201D are a people
          of a city south of Arvad.      The Hamathites, which means \u201Cfortress
          dwellers,\u201D are the people of the city of Hamath, modern Hama in Syria.
          See  ;  ;  .    "
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the Canaanite territory extending from Sidon toward Gerar [[COMMENT(0)]]
        to Gaza  including Sodom,  Gomorrah,  Admah,  and Zeboiim,  as far as Lasha.   '
      comments:
      - number: 10:19
        content: "  Gerar, which means \u201Clodging place,\u201D was a Philistine
          town in Gaza, modern-day Umm.      Gaza, which means \u201Cthe strong one,\u201D
          was a Philistine city in the southwest coastal region of Israel, modern
          Gaza City.      Sodom, which means \u201Cburning,\u201D was a Canaanite
          city located in the region of the Dead Sea, possibly identified with Tell
          el-Hammam in Jordan near the Israeli border, and was destroyed by God\u2019s
          judgment of fire and brimstone. See  .      Gomorrah, which means \u201Csubmersion,\u201D
          was a Canaanite city, perhaps a twin city of Sodom located in the region
          of the Dead Sea.      Admah, which means \u201Cred earth,\u201D was a Canaanite
          city in the Siddim Valley.      Zeboiim, which means \u201Cgazelles,\u201D
          was a neighboring city of Sodom.      Lasha, which means \u201Cfissure,\u201D
          was a city of the Dead Sea Valley.    "
    - name: '20: Descendants of Shem'
      title: Descendants of Shem
      number: 20
      content: These were the descendants of Ham by families, lands, languages, and
        nations.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Shem, the older brother of Japheth, also had sons and was the ancestor
        of all the sons of Eber, who were also known as \u201CHebrews.\u201D  [[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: 10:21
        content: "  Eber, which means \u201Cthe region beyond\u201D or \u201Cthe
          opposite side,\u201D was the eponymous ancestor of the Hebrews.    "
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The sons of Shem were Elam, [[COMMENT(0)]] Assyria,  Arphaxad,  Lud, 
        and Aram. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:22
        content: "  Elam, which means \u201Ceternal one\u201D or \u201Ceternity,\u201D
          settled in Babylonia. His people\u2019s capital city was Susa. See  ; 
          .      Or \u201CAsshur,\u201D the Hebrew word for \u201CAssyria.\u201D     
          Arphaxad, which means \u201Che cursed the breast,\u201D is associated with
          Babylon, and some Jewish scholars identify him as the founder of the Chaldean
          city of Ur, the future home of Abram.      Lud, which means \u201Cstrife,\u201D
          settled in northern Africa and may be the ancestor of the Lydians of Anatolia.     
          Aram, which means \u201Cexalted,\u201D refers to the Arameans who eventually
          settled in Syria. Through their influence the Aramaic language shaped commerce
          and diplomacy.    "
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The sons of Aram were Uz, [[COMMENT(0)]] Hul,  Gether,  and Mash. '
      comments:
      - number: 10:23
        content: "  Uz, which means \u201Cwoodland,\u201D was the land of Job, possibly
          in Arabia.      Hul, which means \u201Ccircle,\u201D was the ancestor of
          a Syrian people group, possibly the Armenians.      Gether, which means
          \u201Cfear,\u201D according to Josephus, was the ancestor of the Bactrians
          of Central Asia.      Or \u201CMeshech\u201D (LXX; see  ).    means \u201Cdrawn
          out.\u201D    "
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Arphaxad was the father of Shelah, [[COMMENT(0)]] the father of Eber.
      comments:
      - number: 10:24
        content: "    means \u201Csent/shot forth [like a prayer].\u201D    "
    - name: '25-26: '
      title: 
      number: 25-26
      content: "Eber was the father of two sons: Peleg, (or \u201CDivision,\u201D 
        [[COMMENT(0)]] for during his lifetime the earth was divided),  and his brother
        Joktan,  the father of Almodad,  Sheleph,  Hazarmaveth,  Jerah,   "
      comments:
      - number: "10:25\u201326"
        content: "  Or \u201CEarthquake.\u201D      \u201CDivision\u201D is a play
          on words for  , which means \u201Cdisperse,\u201D \u201Cdivide,\u201D or
          \u201Ccut into channels.\u201D The Hebrew word  , which means \u201Cearth,\u201D
          is more commonly translated \u201Cland.\u201D In that case, \u201Cthe earth
          was divided\u201D could point to a tectonic dividing of the continents
          during the lifetime of Peleg. The Greeks call the Aegean Sea the \u201CArchi,\u201D
          or the \u201Cfirst sea.\u201D There is some evidence to link this with
          the scientific theory of continental drift; the parting of the continents
          during the days of Peleg. Most scholars, however, view this \u201Cdivision\u201D
          as the dividing of languages and dispersing of nations at the Tower of
          Babel.      Joktan, which means \u201Che will be made little,\u201D was
          the ancestor of various Arabian tribes. His Arabic name means \u201Cwakeful.\u201D       
          means \u201Cnot measured,\u201D or \u201CGod is friend\u201D (LXX).     
          Sheleph, which means \u201Cdrawn out,\u201D was the possible ancestor of
          various Yemenite tribes.      Hazarmaveth, which means \u201Coasis of Mot\u201D
          or \u201Cthe god of death,\u201D was the possible ancestor of people who
          settled east of Yemen. He is equated with modern Hadramawt in Yemen.     
          Jerah, which means \u201Cmoon\u201D or \u201Cmonth,\u201D likely settled
          in south Arabia.    "
